ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend since the contents of the course are important for every cs major student
yes, it is a good course if you want to have an overview of os
Sure. The course is very useful.
Yes, if you want a general understanding of OS and no programming.
I would highly recommend this course if you lack basic knowledge of Operating Systems. It will teach you general principles that can be applied in CS in general.
Course suitable for graduate students and useful for future work.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: As a PhD student, it did not contribute directly to my research area but I did learn fundamental things which allow me to be a better programmer and researcher
OS is very important foundation of CS.
Yes, I always want to reorganize my knowledge of OS, and this course helps.

Even though the topics covered don't directly relate to my research, I found that they were essential to complete my education in Computer Science, and many of the underlying principles covered are applicable to different areas as well.
Learned a lot of newest knowledge in computer science
